	   It took Roman Empire several hundred years of slow decline and decadence before it finally collapsed. That was many centuries ago and things are moving much faster in the global economy of today. The only force that is slowing things down is that no one really wants anything to happen too fast. A sudden collapse of US$ would shake the entire world's economy to it's core and wouldn't benefit anyone. A slow and steady (but firm) winding down is in everyone's best interest. Except for the US of course, but they made their own bed.<div style='float: right;' class='clearfix'>
